18th India International Trade Fair Opens
NEW DELHI , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- The 18th India International Trade Fair opened here Saturday with a call by President Kocheril Raman Narayanan to Indian companies to make their products competitive in the international market .
In a speech read out by Finance Minister Yashwant Sinha on the inauguration of the trade fair , Narayanan said trade and industry had to make combined efforts to improve the economic scenario in the country .
The president urged Indian companies to establish the Indian brand name through quality products and use of latest technology .
He regretted the presence of poverty , unemployment and income disparities in his country , saying it was definitely needed to develop economically sound and efficient technologies for the benefit of masses .
The 18th India International Trade fair , which covers a gross display area of about 140,000 square meters , have been participated by nearly 5,000 Indian companies and some 150 foreign firms from 20 countries .
